<font color="#FF0000">DOC AND CHET</font><br>
<tt>Mon Apr 14 23:49:40 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
Good Morning, Vietnam!<br><br>
I really like that movie title. I like the movie, too. It is honest.<br><br>
Doc,<br><br>
The press seems to be enchanted with your &quot;transformation&quot;. Actually, it was a lot of hard work on your part and a lot of stubbornness on our part. You deserve a day in the sun! Just don't get too toasted!<br><br>
I am watching to see if the 60's crowd takes your challenge. <br>
I have a feeling they will ignore you. Discourse with Lower Slobovians is against some codes of ethical appearances. It is my experience that those who subscribe to codes of ethical appearances employ a hit and run tactic. We will soon see if any of the 60's crowd has the courage of their convictions.<br><br>
Chet,<br><br>
&quot;Maybe that makes those folks another type of adjective?&quot;<br><br>
I think your extension of my comments is well spoken. I will see if I can find a synonym somewhere. Honestly, though, I am developing a loss for words when I encounter people with a bias such as theirs, though my continuing mental image is one of the Jolly Roger.    
